He stresses the importance of mapping the bats before maintenance is carried out on a property since accidental destruction of a single breeding place can kill up to 400 females and young people, and perhaps destroy an entire local population.
The bats are protected and it is illegal to kill them, harass them or disrupt them or destroy their breeding places.
Elisabeth Ferrell, a Scottish member of the Bat Conservation Trust team, has encouraged the audience to help work.
